question: Janet's chickens produce 16 eggs a day. She eats three breakfast cereals every morning, cooks four biscuits for her friends every day. She sells the rest of the eggs at the farmers' market for $2 a day for a fresh chicken. How much money does she make a day at the farmers' market?
How many beads will each beam take up? 2 blue beads and half of the white beads.
Josh decides to try copying a house. He buys it for $80,000 and leaves $50,000 for repairs, which increases the value of the house by 150%. How much profit did he make?
James decides to run three runs three times a week. He runs 60 meters on each run. How many meters does he run in a week?

Wendy feeds each of her chicks three pieces of cornmeal, which includes seeds, nuts, and vegetables that are good for their health. She feeds her chicks three different foods. In the morning, she feeds her flock of chicks 15 pieces of cornmeal, and in the afternoon, she feeds another flock of chicks 25 pieces of cornmeal. If Wendy's flock is 20 chicks, how many pieces of cornmeal will she need to feed her chicks at the last meal of the day?
Kyler goes to the store to buy glasses for his new apartment. $5 for one window, but only 60% off for each second window. Kyler wants to buy 16 windows. How much will they cost?
Toulouse has twice as many sheep as Charleston. Charleston has 4 times as many sheep as Seattle. How many sheep do Toulouse, Charleston and Seattle have in common if Seattle has 20 sheep?

Carla is caching a 200 GB file. By default, she can cache 2 GB/minute, but 40% of the way through the cache, Windows Update forces a restart to load, which takes 20 minutes. After that, Carla must restart to cache from the beginning. What cache is needed to cache the file?

After driving for 3 hours at a speed of 60 km/h, John turned around as he realized that he had forgotten several important things at home. He tried to get home in 4 hours but spent the first 2 hours in traffic jams. He spent the next half hour driving at a speed of 30mph, before driving for the remaining 4 hours at 80mph. At the end of the 4 hours, how far was he from home?
For the first 40 hours of work in a week, Eliza is paid $10 per hour, plus 1.2 times the overtime. If Eliza works 45 hours this week, how much will she get for the week?

One new program had 60 outcomes in the first month. In the second month the number of outcomes in the first month dropped three times, but in the third month it decreased by 30%. What was the total outcome of the program in three months?
Toola went to the bakery and bought a variety of pastas.She bought 3 cans of donuts for $68 each, 2 cans of biscuits for $80, and 6 cans of biscuits for $55 each.How much was the total cost?

Carlos has an apple tree. It costs $90 to plant the tree. If he grows 7 apples a year, he can sell them for $1.5 each. It costs $3 a year to water and feed the tree. How many years does it take before he starts making money from the apple tree?

Melanie is a house-to-house saleswoman. She sold one-third of her empty space to a green house, 2 more to a red house, and the remaining half to a brown house. If Melanie had 5 empty spaces left, how many would she start with?
In a dance class of 20 students, 20% are enrolled in modern dance, 25% in jazz, and the remainder in hip-hop.

A trader needs to choose between two buying plans: $5,000 worth of goods or $8,000 worth of electronics.His financial advisor predicts that the price of electronics will rise by 2.5% in the same month.If the trader chooses to make a profit at the end of the month, how much profit will it make?
Starting from San Rafael, two trains travel westward, each traveling 80 miles [80 km].The next day, they travel northward, covering 150 miles [150 km].
If she worked 50 weeks a year, 35 hours a week as a teacher, and 15 hours a week as a coach, what would her salary be?
Claire makes 3 egg omelettes for breakfast every morning. How many eggs does she lay in 4 weeks?

Marisa walks the 12 miles. It takes her 1 hour to walk the first 4 miles, and then another hour to walk the next 2 miles. If you want her average speed to be 4 miles per hour, how fast (in miles per hour) should she walk the remaining distance?

I have 10 liters of vodka which is two thirds water, I would like to add 15 liters of pineapple juice which is three fifths water. But if I pour one liter of vodka, how much water is in the remaining 24 liters?
Raymond and Samantha have a daughter.Raymond was born 6 years before Samantha.Raymond was 23 years old when he had a son.If Samantha is now 31 years old, how long ago was Raymond's son born?

Bill sells DVDs. He has 8 customers on Tuesday. His first 3 customers each buy one DVD. His next 2 customers each buy 2 DVDs. His last 3 customers don't buy any DVDs. How many DVDs did Bill sell on Tuesday?
A shaman runs 2 centimeters per hour of sleep. How many centimeters does a shaman shorten after sleeping from 1:00 PM to 5:00 PM?
Kyle purchased a copy of last year's bestseller for $19.50, which was 25% off the original price.

Mary ordered a chicken dish for $12, 5 cans of milk for $3 each, 4 apples for $1.50 each, and a box of pizzas.Mary paid $50 in total. If the box was $8.50 each, how many boxes of pizzas did Mary order?
Mishkan bought 3 shorts, 3 pants, and 3 shoes. A pair of shorts cost $16.50 each; a pair of pants cost $2.50 each; and a pair of shoes cost $42. How much did Mishkan spend on all the items?
Cynthia eats one ice cream a night. She buys a carton of 15 ice cream for $4.00 a carton. How much does she spend on ice cream after 60 days?

Henry made two stops on his 60-mile bike trip. The first stop was after 20 miles. His second stop was 15 miles before the end of his trip. How many miles did he travel between his first and second stops?

While shopping for shoes, Gloria found a pair of shoes that would fit her budget. However, she had to choose from a collection of boots and two high-heeled shoes that cost less than five dollars. If one of the high-heeled shoes was $33 and the other was twice as expensive, how much would the shoe cost?
The ages of Darrell and Allen are in the ratio 7:11. If their combined present age is 162 years, Allen's life expectancy is 10 years.

Gunter is trying to count the jelly beans in the jar. He asks his friends how many they think are in the jar. One says 80. Another 20 says more than half of the original. A third says 25% more than the original. What is their average estimate?

John takes care of 10 dogs. Each dog takes 0.5 hours a day to take care of their daily walks and chores. Each dog takes 0.5 hours a day to walk and take care of their business. How many hours a week does it take to take care of dogs?
The Grech has 110 coins. The silver coin is 30 times more valuable than the gold coin. How many gold coins does Grech have?
Siobhan has 2 fewer pearls than Aaron. Aaron has 5 more pearls than half of Raymond's pearls. If Raymond has 40 pearls, how many pearls does Siobhan have?
Mike plays ping pong for 40 minutes. In the first 20 minutes he scores 4 points. In the second 20 minutes he scores an additional 25% points. How many points did he score in total?
Terry eats 2 cookies a day. Currently 4 cookies are sold for $5.00 each. How much does a cookie cost in 30 days?

John plans to sell all his toys and use the money to buy a video game. He has 13 sets of Legos and sells them for $15 each. He ends up buying 8 video games for $20 each and has $5 left. How many Legos do I still have in my collection?
John runs 60 miles a week. He runs 3 days a week. The first day he runs for 3 hours and a half and the other two days. How fast does he run?
If she could run three miles an hour, how many miles would she run in an hour if she ran a third of the way and walked two thirds of the way?
Brando's iPhone is four times older than Ben's. Ben's iPhone is twice as old as Suzie's. If Suzie's iPhone is 1 year old, how old is Brando's iPhone?

The giant Perge, perched on the summit of Mount Farbo, blew flames at anything within 1,000 feet. The golden spear, the only weapon known to have stolen the dragon, could be fired at a distance of 400 feet, where the fire could reach the dragon. But with the sapphire in its hand, the spear was three times stronger than without the gem. If so, how far away from the dragon's fire could Pauline stand and strike the golden spear again?

Grandma Johnson cooked five apples for the fireman's lunch. She cut each apple into eight pies and placed five pies on the dining table for the guests to serve themselves. By the end of the evening, after the guests had eaten their pies, there were 14 pies left. How many pies did each guest receive?

According to the dietary information, one pound of potato chips has 250 calories per meal. If one pound of potato chips has 5, how many grams would you eat if you had 2,000 calories per day and had eaten 1,800 calories before?

Charlie wants to sell his cheese. He can make a total of 10 cheeses for each cheese. He sells his cheese and tomatoes for $10.00 a week. If he sells his cheese for $2.00 each, what is the net profit if he makes 20 cheeses?

While Meredith is a freelance blogger, she writes about health topics and delivers them to clients on a daily basis as part of her routine. One blog post takes an average of 4 hours to research and write. Last week she wrote 5 articles on Monday, and 2/5 more on Tuesday than she did on Monday. Last Wednesday she wrote twice as many articles as she did on Tuesday. She spent a total of six hours writing in three days.

Before leaving for her job at the coffee shop, Candice put 80 pieces of paper in her bag. On the way to the store, she stopped and bought a package of Italian souvenirs; at work, she put a letter of remembrance on each of the 220 different cups of coffee. If there were 23 letters of remembrance left, how many letters of remembrance were in the package she bought?

John buys red carbide twice as much as blue carbide. The red carbide costs 50% more than the blue carbide. He spent $200 on the blue carbide which cost $40 each. How much did he spend on the blue carbide?
Tracy used a four-foot long pole to support the tomato plants in the garden. The pole was cut six inches long. How many broken eggs did she find?
Richard lives in a 15-story apartment building. Each floor consists of 8 units, occupying 3/4 of the building. How many of the total units are unoccupied?
Lloyd owns an egg farm. Her chicks produce 252 eggs a day and sell the last of them for $2 each. How many eggs does Lloyd make in a week?
The Tom can travel 10 miles per hour. It sails from 1 to 4 PM. Then it turns back at 6 mph. How long does it take to return?

Uriah's book bag is too heavy for him. He has to lift 15 pounds. His books weigh 1/4 of a pound each and his toys weigh 1/2 of a pound each. If he carries 30 books, how many toys does he have to lift?

A mechanic charges different rates for each truck wheel and truck repair. For each truck wheel repaired, the mechanic charges $60 and for each truck wheel repaired, the mechanic charges $40. In each case, the mechanic repairs 6 truck wheels and 4 truck wheels. On Fridays, the mechanic does not repair 12 truck wheels or any truck wheels. On the day of high earnings, how much more did the mechanic earn?

The Dabtifire brothers are driving home in their car with 7 bunnies who were raised in the shade of local wildlife when their mother calls to tell them that their two house bunnies have recently given birth to four children. She says that Pachy, the first bunny, has three times the number of children as the adopted one, while Trisha, the other bunny, has 12.
Jean has 30 lollipops. Jean eats 2 of the lollipops. With the rest of the lollipops, she wants to put Jean 2 lollipops in one basket. How many baskets can Jean fill?
Peter plans to go to the movies this week. He gets regular tickets for $7 and popcorn for $7. With $42 for a week, how many times can he go to the movies?

The bridge can carry no more than 5000 pounds. Transport vehicles loaded with boxes weighing 15 pounds each cross the bridge. The combined weight of the driver and the cargo vehicle is 3755 pounds. How many boxes can be loaded onto the cargo vehicle without exceeding the weight limit?

Stephen ordered a grocery order online. His final payment was $40.00. Since this was a form of transportation purchase, they signed off on a 25% charge on his final total and charged him $3.00 in transportation fees. Stephen added a $4.00s tip. After the additional charge, what was the final price of the food that Stephen ordered?
A forest is described as having 6 clusters of 20 berries each and 67 individual berries planted in the forest. How many trees are there in total?
If a bowl contains 25 eggs, 1 of them is raw, 20% is unripe, 2 are raw, and the rest is good. How many eggs are good?
Janet purchased jewelry for her daughter, paid $500 for the equipment, paid another $800 for the consultant, and paid 10 percent of the cost for insurance.

If Marcie works for a company for 40 years, she receives an annual pension of $50,000. After 20 years, she is entitled to an annual pension of 5%. If she retires after 30 years, what will her retirement age be?

Alena paid $140 a month for her broadcasting services. If the broadcaster charged her less than 10% of her first-half salary for the first half of the year and then charged her less than 10% of her second-half salary for the second half of the year, the total salary she paid for her broadcasting services at the end of the year would be taxed.

Sophia, who is considering a road trip, wants to know how far she can go with one tank of gas. After the last 100 miles, she still needs to fill up her tank with 4 gallons of gas. According to the manufacturer's contract, her car has 12 gallons of gas. How many miles can Sophia travel with one tank of gas?
Jim spent 2 hours watching TV and then decided to lie in bed and read for half an hour. He does this 3 times a week. In 4 weeks, how many hours does he spend watching TV and reading?

In a basketball tournament, four schools compete. Each school sends a girls basketball team and a boys basketball team. Each team has 5 players. Each school sends a coach to each team. How many players each school sends?
A treasure hunter found a buried treasure chest filled with precious stones - 175 diamonds, 35 rubies less than a diamond, and twice as many emeralds.
At Dr. Wertz's school, there are twice as many boys as girls. If there are 60 girls for every teacher and 5 students, how many teachers are there?
Belle starts with a certain amount of money. After that, for 8 weeks, she earns $5 per week. At the end of 8 weeks, if she has a total of $100, how much money did Belle start with?
Judy teaches 5 dance classes, 8 classes every day, weekdays and Sundays. If each class has 15 students and she charges $15.00 per student, how much money does she make in 1 week?
If Kelia has two recipes, one with 20 recipes and the other with twice as many recipes, how many recipes does Kelia have to read to prepare the two meals?
Tommy is raising money for his charity, selling a few apples for $3 and a few cakes for $4. How much money would Tommy make if he sold 43 apples and 23 cakes?
Sheila bought five mobile phones for $150 each for 3 months. Each unit is charged 2% interest. How much does Sheila pay per month for 3 months?

Artie has a flea market at the Farmers' Market. He sells three types of flea: yellow, black, and brown. He usually sells yellow for $2.74 a bushel, black for $1.87 a bushel, and brown for $2.12 a bushel. Artie doesn't change today so he decides to keep all his prices around the dollar. How much would Artie make if he sold 12 boxes of yellow, 9 boxes of black, and 17 boxes of brown?

Luke is spending time building a sand tower on the shore, and he eventually figures out that each level of the sand tower is half a square foot on the lower level. If he built a 4-story sand tower instead of a 16-square-foot top level, what is the average square foot per level?

Cecilia bought a new cat litter. According to her veterinarian, she will need to feed 1 litter of cat food per day for the first 180 days. After that, she will need to feed 2 litter of cat food per day for the rest of her life. If a litter of cat food contains 110 litter of cat food, how many litter of cat food will Cecilia use in the first year?
If Raymond weighs half as much as Sarah, if Sarah weighs four times as much as David, and if Sarah weighs 400 pounds, the difference is about as much as Raymond and David weigh.
Vincent could buy 3 cans for $2.50 or 2 cans for $1. How much money would he save to buy 18 cans at a lower price?
John raises a dog. Delivering the dog to a groomer costs $100. The groomer, being a new customer, gives him a 30% discount. How much does the grooming cost?
Two girls each received one-sixth of a pint [24 L]; then one young man received one pint [6 L]; how many pints of water remained?
He bought 21 and received 23 for his birthday, 9 of which he gave to his sister, and 28 he used to print invitations.
Grace weighs 125 pounds. Alex is 4 times 2 pounds lighter than Grace. How many pounds do they weigh together?
Dan plants 3 rose bushes, each with 25 bunches of roses, each with 8 rose petals. How many petals are there in total?
One soccer team played 22 games. They won 8 more than they lost. How many did they win?

Jean is sewing a winter coat on an old commemorative t-shirt. He has one t-shirt from each holiday. Each t-shirt is his winter coat. Each row is made of leaves from a different holiday year. He goes on four holidays a year and has been on vacation since he was 23 years old. He is now 34 years old. In total, how many winter coats does he have?

Greg has an alarm clock that rings three times a day as a reminder. When the alarm clock goes off, he keeps ringing until Greg stops. The first time it goes off, he rings four times. The second time it goes off, he rings three times more than the first time. The third time it rings half the second time. In total, how many times did the alarm clock ring?

The company pays each of its employees $600 a month. The company has a salary policy of increasing the annual salary of each of its employees by 10% of the initial salary for those who have been with the company for five years. If Sylvie has just worked for the company for 5 years as of last December, what is her salary after three more years of service?
Harald's first recording of Marilyn's sold 10 times as many copies as the 88,000 combined, but how many copies did Harold sell?
A Christian who is planning a birthday party, needs a gift of 0.75 for each guest, because 1/4 of the participants will be absent. She invited 16 friends. Each one needs a gift of $2. How much?

Ted T-Rex planned to bring the dinosaurs to the park. He knew that an adult dinosaur would eat 10 pounds of the dinosaur, and a child would eat half of the adult. If there were 20 adults and 5 children in the park, how many pounds of the dinosaur would he bring to the park if he hoped to have enough to feed them all?
Jan has three times as many owls as Marcia. Marcia has two more owls than Cindy. If Cindy has four owls, how many owls do the three of them have in total?

Some vehicles passed through the first 15 minutes of the traffic closure, and then 20 more vehicles passed through in the remaining 15 minutes. 5 vehicles took the exit from the line and did not drive through the traffic closure. If there were initially 30 motorcycles on the motorway, how many vehicles passed through the traffic closure in the first 15 minutes?

Mary is an avid gardener. She has recently acquired 18 new potted plants from her favorite nursery. Previously she had 2 potted plants in each of the 40 windows of her large country house. Filled with generosity, she decides to give one potted plant from each corner of the garden to friends and family.

Jerome had 4 friends who came to visit him on a given day. The first friend rang the doorbell 20 times before Jerome opened the door, the second friend rang the doorbell 1/4 times more than Jerome's first friend. The third friend rang the doorbell 10 times more than Jerome's first friend. If the fourth friend rang the doorbell 60 times, how many times did the doorbell ring?

Solon had to read page 4 of his Science textbook, page 20 of his Social Studies textbook, page 7 of his History textbook, and page 8 of his Geography textbook. On Monday, Solon read page 15. If he had 4 more days to finish all his reading, on average, how many pages would he need to read in a day?

On Thursdays, he finishes his homework early and watches an hour-long episode and a 30-minute show. On Fridays, he watches two one-hour episodes because he can get up for the weekend. In total, he watches 7 hours of TV, so how many 30-minute episodes does he watch on Wednesdays?

Henry is making a cake for a national baking competition. Last year he wanted to make twice as much. When he finishes baking, he realizes that he actually baked 15 more cakes than he had thought. He leaves 5 of his cakes in the bag to freeze, and now he has a total of 110 cakes. How many cakes did Henry make last year?

A local gas station is selling gas for $3.00 per gallon. An app company is offering a cash back of $20.00 per gallon if you fill the station with gas. If someone buys 10 gallons of gas, how much gas will they have with them, after cash back?

Marcel and Beatrice have a competition to see who can eat the most fruit in the cluster, so they interpret what they find. It is interesting that someone made a mistake: Beatrice's is 2 inches high and 24 inches long, and Marcel's is 3 inches high and 14 inches long. If they both ate as much as they wanted, how much did they eat on average?

If each class has four teachers, then each teacher has two teachers. If each class has three teachers, then each teacher has four teachers.
Ryan plants 2 flowers a day in his field. After 15 days if he doesn't grow 5 flowers how many flowers does he have?

Sasha, after buying some wood, realizes that the price of the wood has gone up by 50% in the last few months. She decides to sell because she has left over. She has ten 2 x 4 x 10 boards left over, each of which she paid her $10 for. She also has five 4 x 4 x 10 boards, each of which she bought for $16 each. The customs officer at the main port of Coast Cleanup counted 2 containers of imported vehicles, each containing 5 vehicles.The next day more containers were brought in, bringing the total number of vehicles at the port to 30.Assuming each container has 5 vehicles, the number of containers recorded on the second day is zero.

Adrienne's total salary was 30 percent more than Leah's. After four years, his salary had increased, which was 40 percent more than what he had been earning four years earlier. If Adrienne and Leah's salary had increased at the same time, and Adrienne had earned $40,000 four years earlier, what would their total salary have been four years later?
Miguel uses 2 sheets of paper per week for his artwork. If there are 30 sheets on each sheet, how many sheets will he use per month?

Morisette and Kael were asked to bring fruit. Morisette brought 5 apples and 8 peaches, while Kael brought twice the number of apples and half the number of peaches than Morisette. How many fruits do they have in total?

On Monday, Sadie slept eight hours; on the next two days, she slept less than two hours each because she had assignments to complete; and if she slept an extra hour on the last two days of the week, how many hours did she sleep in total that week?
Rosie can run 10 miles per hour for 3 hours. Then she runs 5 miles per hour. How many miles can she run in 7 hours?
Jenny, who works in her mother's office, has a stack of 60 letters that need to be typed and a stack of pre-printed letters that need to be typed on about a third of the letters.

Later, her father-in-law bought five new bags of chicken soup for her, which she made with three of the same bags of chicken soup that she had used to make her sandwich. Later, when she went to set the table, she had a total of 12 bags of chicken soup.
Dylan needed chicken sausage and fish sausage on each plate. he bought 38 chicken sausages and 6 fish sausages instead of chicken sausage. how many sausages did Dylan buy altogether?
Since moving to a new school, Amy has had 20 more friends than Lily does. If Lily has 50 friends, how many friends do Lily and Amy have in common?
Dillon is sent to the store to buy four beans, 20 beans, and 10 beans. If each beans costs $15, how much will he spend in total?

A hospital sees 500 people a day. Each patient is seen for an average of 24 minutes. Doctors charge the hospital $150 per hour, and the hospital charges patients $200 per hour. How much profit does the hospital make from these visits?

In May, Joseph's expenses were $500; by June, they had dropped to $60.

Pam and Fred went to a carnival. Pam had climbed the roller coaster 2 times and Fred had climbed it 4 times. Then they each decided to try the luge 2 times. If each ladder issued 6 tickets, how many tickets did they use that day?
On Monday, Walt walked four miles. On Tuesday, he walked six times the mile he walked on Monday. His total mileage from Monday to Wednesday was 41 miles. How many miles did he walk on Wednesday?
Tom receives car washes 4 times a month. If each car wash costs $15 (U.S.), how much will he pay in a year?

Rory orders 2 subs for $7.50 each, 2 chips for $1.50 each, and 2 cookies for $1.00 each. If the delivery charge is increased by 20%, she wants to increase it by $5.00. What does her delivery charge?

John buys milk for $2, eggs for $3, light bulbs for $3, balls for $3, duck traps for $4. If there is a 10% tax on all non-food items, how much does everything cost?

Kim started her own cleaning business and calculated how much profit she would make from her customers. She already had 3 customers, but she was talking to 5 other potential customers, feeling confident enough to include them in her calculations. Each household needed 2 sheets of laundry and one pack of clothes to clean. The cost per sheet of laundry was $2, and the cost per pack of clothes was $5. That's the only difference. The average weekly income per household was $92.
John had a 10 hectare pineapple field. There were 100 pineapples in one hectare. John could harvest his pineapples in 3 months. How many pineapples could John harvest in a year?

John collects the toys from his room on the floor. He puts them in a box that weighs 500 grams, another that weighs more than 500 grams, and another that weighs a quarter of a gram. How many blocks does John take if he puts them all together?

Debra tracks a canyon to see how many canyons come and go in a day. In the first 6 hours she sees 30 canyons leave the canyon, and then in the next 6 hours she sees 1/2 more canyons return. She sees twice as many canyons as she first saw flying out of the corn and leaving in the next 6 hours. Then all the canyons that went before her return to the canyon in the next 6 hours without returning. How many canyons did Debra see return to the canyon in the last 6 hours?

Brittany and her mother go to the museum. The entrance fee is $12 for adults and $10 for children. The British mother gives the cashier the money for 1 child ticket and 1 adult ticket. If she finds $8 in change, how much money, in dollars, did she give the cashier?
Charlie has three times as many Facebook friends as Dorothy. James has four times as many Facebook friends as Dorothy. If Charlie has 12 Facebook friends, how many Facebook friends does James have?

Steve and Tim decide to see who can get home from school faster. Steve is allowed to ride his bike because he lives farther away than Tim. Steve lives 3 miles away from the school and can cycle 440 miles per minute. Tim lives 2 miles away from the school. If Tim can skateboard 264 miles per minute, how long will the winner wait at home before finishing the race?

Shawnda decides that the kids in her neighborhood can actually use the bicycle tire service. She decides that the best way to charge it is with a car tire. She spends 25 cents each for a car tire tire. On the first day, 5 cyclists pass by to have both of their tires blown. 3 people pass by to have all three of their bicycle tires blown. Finally, someone actually passes by with a bicycle. How many dollars did she get that day?
Carl bought ten packs of cookies. Each packet of cookies contained six cookies. Each cookie cost $0.10. How much change would Carl get if he paid with $10?

Dave bought a large packet of french fries and ate fourteen, before a hungry seagull snatched the packet from his hand. When the seagull landed, he ate less than half of the french fries Dave had eaten. Then three pigeons threatened him away from the food, each eating three pieces of french fries. Later, a raccoon stole two-thirds of the remaining french fries. The rabbits took the last five french fries and left. How many french fries were in the packet when Dave bought them?

On Mondays, Wednesdays, and Fridays, a Kimo student has 1 three-hour class per day. He has 2 two-hour classes per day on Tuesdays and Thursdays. There are 16 weeks of classes in a semester. How many hours does Kimo spend in school in a semester?
Each day, Bill makes 300 rolls, 120 chocolate croissants, and 60 bags - each roll is four inches long, each croissant is six inches long, and each bag is six feet [2 m] long.

The zookeeper feeds all the monkeys in the zoo. He orders all the monkeys from the local farm for 2 months. If a thief needs 200 monkeys, a gorilla needs 400 monkeys, and a baboon needs 100 monkeys per month, how many monkeys should he order to stay for 2 months?

Blake and Kelly are competing to see who can run the fastest in 15 minutes. They decide to work on a 100-yard football field. Blake runs back and forth 15 times. Kelly runs back and forth once, then decides she doesn't want to run into Blake, and starts running back and forth to the 40-yard line.
Raphael went out to buy some school supplies. He bought a set of 4 for $1.5, a set of 2 for $4, and a set of paper towels for $20. How much did Raphael spend on everything?
Finn watches 11 tadpoles swimming in the reservoir. Suddenly he sees 6 of them hiding under a lily pad, then he sees 2 hiding under a rock. How many tadpoles can Finn now see in the reservoir?
A water tank is 17 meters deep on Monday.On Tuesday the tank had 7 feet more water.On Tuesday the water is two-thirds as deep as it was on Tuesday.What is the water depth of the tank on Wednesday?

Anakin and Locsin went to the beach today. Anakin caught 10 starfish, 6 seahorses, and 3 clownfish. Locsin caught 5 starfish less than Anakin, 3 seahorses less than Anakin, and 2 clownfish more than Anakin. How many fish did they catch?
If a coin is worth $20 and its value increases by 20% in two months, how much would a coin be worth after 36 months?

In each room there are different toys: 5 red cars, 3 action figures and a doll. The doll cost up to 3 action figures and a red car cost $4. How much are each of the toys worth, $5 for each action figure?

Jackie is trying to decide whether to do her own tax filing or hire an accountant. If she does her own tax filing, she will be able to work freelance for 3 hours less, losing $35 an hour. The accountant will only be paid $90. If she hires an accountant, how much extra money will she have?

For his 30th birthday, Elvira chooses to give him a new computer with many kitchen appliances. She has a generous family budget of €1500 and thinks that she can afford to buy one outfit. She goes to the computer store and chooses a machine that costs €1090 and has a screen, keyboard and mouse. She also gets a €157 scanner, a €74 CD burner and a €102 printer. How much money does she have left for her clothes?

Neighbor Sandra gives her a bag of 9 eggs every time she takes care of their daughter. She needs 3 eggs to make a Spanish flannel. If Sandra is given 15 Spanish flannels to make for her school to save money, how many times does Sandra have to take care of a baby?
Seth is twice Brooke's age, and they were married two years later, when they were both 28.
Jimmy has twice as much money as Ethel has. Ethel has $8, and how much money does Jimmy have?
Pancho walks 20 miles a day, except on weekends when he walks 10 miles. How many miles does he walk in a week?

The marching band is ordering new uniforms. Each uniform has a $25 coffeemaker, a triple coffeemaker jacket, and pants that average the cost of a coffeemaker and a coffeemaker jacket. How much are each uniform worth in total?

Jake is walking through the Entomology Museum. He sees 80 rodents each with 8 feet, 90 insects each with 6 feet, and 3 rare mutant invertebrates each with 10 feet. How many feet does Jake see in total?

There are four birds on a caboose. Sally Two is three years older than Granny Red. Granny Red is twice as old as Sally Four. If Sally Four is equal to Sally Thirty-two and Sally Thirty-two is 8 years old, what is the total age of the four birds?

Jessica is trying to figure out how much to pay off all of her loans each month. Her student loans have a minimum payment of $300 per month, her credit cards have a minimum payment of $200 per month, and her husband's loans have a minimum payment of $500 per month. If Jessica wanted to pay 50% less than that, how much would she pay off in a year?

Billie barbecues the skin of the rabbit and has a few to prepare to make the rabbit salad for his large family gathering. Because of its size, he has 60 rabbits to pass through. Since the rabbits are roughly the same size, each takes about the same amount of time to peel and cut. Billie takes about a minute and a half to peel a rabbit, but for some it only takes about 5 seconds. How long does it take to finish making the rabbit?

Juan and his brother Carlos are selling a gallon of beets for $3.00 and a gallon of sugar for $2.00 each, so they sell 20 coconuts for $0.50 each. If they make $25 profit, how much do they spend on beets?
Of the 240 Asians in the tournament, 80 were Japanese and the rest were Chinese.If there were 60 boys in the Chinese team, how many girls were in the Chinese team?

Zayed spends 1/4 of his salary on rent, 1/3 on car fuel, and donates half of the rest to his favorite charity. $200 for his daughter's weekly expenses, and $700 for his wife's shopping and other household expenses. If Zayed earns $6,000 a month, how much money would he still have after all these expenses and donations?
Rani Monik has ten more crabs than Bo, who has 4 fewer crabs. If Bo has 40 craps, then calculate the total number of craps the three of them have together.
Lloyd was paid $10 per hour for the Math tutorials. The first week he gave 5 hours of tutorials, the second week he gave 8 hours of tutorials. How much did he get for the first two weeks?
Two candidates are competing to represent the class at Sarah's school.The winner receives 3/4 of the votes and 80 of the total votes in the class, depending on the number of votes received.

Sandra, a florist in the area, was displeased that Fred's order was incomplete. She ordered four times as much red rice as white carnations, and 200 plastic lilies, five times as many white carnations. Sandra decided that if the red rice was not delivered by 5 p.m., she would have to change suppliers.
Jean is two years older than Mark. Two years ago Mark was half a year older than Jean by 5 years. If Jean is 30 years old, how old is Jean?

Two teams of track runners compete in the 4 and 400 meter races; each race team consists of four members who each run 400 meters, or one lap, around a fixed track area. One of the two teams is very agile, with each member running their 400 meters in exactly 55 seconds. The other team is less agile; their first run is their 400 meters in 60 seconds and after each lap they run the next race 3 seconds faster than the previous race. Using this information, which team is the fastest second winner?
Jerry is copying a hexadecimal digit. What is the probability of copying more than 3 digits (expressed in decimals) than copying two consecutive integers?
Jenna and her mother picked a few flowers from their garden. Jenna picked half of her mother's flowers. If her mother had 20 flowers, how many flowers would the two of them pick?

If Russell works in a pet store, he distributes grass among the chickens. If the chickens are kept in groups of 3 tents, each receives 6 grass pieces. If the hamsters are kept in 10 tents alone, each receives 5 grass pieces.
Mandy owes Benedict $100. They have agreed to a 2% monthly interest. How much should Mandy pay Benedict if she can pay after 3 months?

If a merchant buys a sack of wheat from a farmer for $20 a sack. If each sack costs $2 to transport from the farm to the warehouse, and if the merchant sells each sack for $30 and makes a total profit of $400, how many sacks did he sell?

The three friends spent $20.25 for 3 tickets to the show. They also spent $4.50 less on food than on tickets. They also travelled on 2 separate stairs, which cost $33 each. If they agreed to share all expenses equally, how much would each of them pay?
John collects peaches for 3 hours. He can collect 2 peaches in a minute. How many peaches can a peach collect?
Chickens need to eat about 3.5 pounds of insects per week to survive. If there is a flock of ten chickens, how many pounds of insects do they need per day?
Tom plants 10 trees a year. He cuts 2 trees a year. He starts with 50 trees. After 10 years, 30% of the trees will die. How many trees are left?

Sue lives in an amusement park. One weekend, the neighbors decided to play a joke on Sue. On Friday morning, the neighbors put 18 pink flamingos on Sue's front porch. On Saturday morning, the neighbors took one-third of the flamingos back and painted them white, and the newly painted white flamingos were put back on Sue's front porch. Then on Sunday morning, they added another 18 pink flamingos to the collection. By Sunday afternoon, how many more pink flamingos were out than white flamingos?
Violet wants to buy a new pair. She has prepared $20 for the purchase if she needs five different colors. Each pair costs $2. How much change does she see?
A coin is worth $1.20 per coin and $0.30 per coin. What is the value of 8 coins?
200 pounds of carrots distributed to 40 restaurants in a particular city. Each restaurant receives 2 pounds of carrots. How many pounds of carrots are not used?
There are exactly 23786 inhabitants in the city of Soda. They include 8417 men and 9092 women. The remaining population is made up of children. How many children are there in Soda?

Elaine initially had 20 Pokemon cards. A month later she collected three times that number. In the second month she collected fewer than 20 cards than in the first month. In the third month she collected twice as many Pokemon cards as in the first and second months. How many Pokemon cards does she now have in total?

Mark is a copywriter. He sends the same amount of articles per week to two different publishers, who each pay him differently for each article. Publisher B pays Mark twice as much as Publisher A. If Mark publishes a total of 1,000 articles per week, Publisher A pays him 5 cents per article. In a week, how much money does Mark make?
Baldur draws water from a well - five buckets in the morning and six buckets in the afternoon. If each bucket holds five liters of water, how many liters of water does he get each day?

John wins a prize at his workplace. The prize consists of a one-time cash award of $5000 and a 5% salary increase. If he earns $2000 per week, how much money did he earn that year if he earned the prize every week and on the first day of the year?
Josie grows vines on 10 acres. Each acre produces 5 tons of wine per year, while each ton of grapes produces 2 barrels of wine. How many barrels of wine does her farm produce per year?

Carl's favorite food is sandwiches. This week he ate one sandwich every day for lunch, and used 2 sandwiches on each sandwich. Three days a week he ate an omelet for breakfast rather than an egg and an omelet for a sandwich. He made a big meal of pasta and sandwiches and used 8 sandwiches to save him for lunch that week. How many sandwiches did he use?
Janet had 22 green pencils and 10 yellow pencils, and then she bought 6 bags of purple pencils and 2 bags of red pencils - 9 pencils in each purple pencil and 6 pencils in each red pencil.
If Brinley scored 89, 71, 92, 100, and 86 on the first five exams, what score would she need on the sixth exam to get an average of 93?

Michael enjoys cycling. He does it at least five times a week and regularly covers 25 kilometers. He did it for four weeks, then decided to cycle only twice a week, but regularly covers 60 kilometers, and did it for three weeks. How many kilometers did Michael cover in total?

Joe's bag contains a Halloween caramel, 25 chocolates, and 80 apple caramels. Each chocolate caramel weighs twice as much as a caramel apple. If each chocolate caramel weighs 40g, how much does Joe's bag of caramels weigh, in grams?

Rose went to the store on Monday and bought 4 cakes. On Tuesday, she went to a different store and bought three times the number of cakes. On Wednesday, she went to another store and bought five times the number of cakes she had bought on Tuesday. How many cakes did she buy three days later?
The total cost of purchasing the 20 balls is $1200 less than the total cost of half a dozen shares sold for $6,000 each.

Sarah wants to buy a new jacket and 2 pairs of shoes for herself. The jacket she wants is $30 and each pair of shoes is $20. Sarah takes care of 4 children in the neighborhood, each time she takes care of a child she gets $5. Her parents pay her $4 for every time she cuts the grass. If Sarah saved $10 before she started taking care of the baby, how many times would she have to cut the grass before she could buy a jacket and shoes?

Jerry has a flock of chickens. The red chickens lay 3 eggs a day, and the white chickens lay 5 eggs a day. Jerry collects 42 eggs a day. If two white chickens have more red eggs, how many red eggs do they have?
Gary enjoys strolling along the edge of the local park, which is a rectangle of about one and a half miles by six miles.

While in the dollar store, Sloan counted 100 customers entering the store. The next day she counted 50 more customers than the first day. If the total number of customers on the third day was 500, how many customers did she count on the third day?

Jerry had two barrels, each of which made 4 gallons of water per minute. 4 minutes ago, the big barrel held twice as much water as the smaller barrel. Now the big barrel holds four times as much water as the smaller barrel. How much water does the smaller barrel hold?
Lori wants to buy a pair of shoes for $320 and a matching belt for $32. Her part-time job pays her $8.00 an hour. How many hours does she have to work before she can make her purchase?
Janet borrowed $2000 and promised to pay back 10% more of the money. If she had to pay $165 a month for 12 months, how much would Janet have left over in that time?
There are 4 roses in a bush. There are 7 more roses in a bush. How many bushes are there in a bush?
Adrian is three times as old as Harriet, and Harriet is half as old as Zack. If Harriet is now 21 years old, the average age is three years in three years.
Four students scored a total of 251 points per board game. Naomi scored 68 points. Yuri scored 10 more than Naomi and Briana scored 17 points more than Naomi. Jojo scored how many points?

Carmen takes 10 minutes to complete a puzzle game, and 5 minutes to complete a sudoku puzzle game. Last weekend she solved 3 crossword puzzles and 8 sudoku puzzles. How much time did she spend playing these games?
One tank holds 120 liters of water, and Celle used 90 liters of the tank to irrigate her small field and then collected twice as much rainwater as before.
Andy stands 90 degrees lower than geranium and 40 degrees lower than petunias. How many degrees does he stand in total?
One company spends $15,000 on advertising for one year, and then a third of that amount for the next year.
Carlos rents a boat for $30 an hour, and Ben rents a raft for $18 an hour. If Carlos rents the boat for 3 hours and Ben rents the raft for 5 hours, how much rent would they pay in total?

Andrew plans to travel by road from New Jersey to Rochester. It takes 6 days by bus to travel from New Jersey to Rochester and half a mile by car. If he plans to travel by bus to Rochester and back by car from Rochester, how many days will it take?

James is counting his Pokemon cards. He has 30 types of fire, 20 types of rain, and 40 types of water. If he loses 8 of the water and buys 14 types of rain, what is the percent chance (sorted to the nearest integer) that the randomly drawn card is the water type?

Chad ordered to make his own burrito for lunch. The basic burrito is $6.50. He added extra meat for $2.00, extra bread for $1.00, avocado for $1.00, and 2 pieces of salt for $0.25 each. He decided to enhance his meal with an additional $3.00 that included chips and drinks. He had a $5.00 gift card that expired. How much debt did he have?

Kalinda is making a 360-degree puzzle game with her mother. Kalinda can add 4 puzzles per minute by default. Her mother can add half as many puzzles per minute to Kalinda by default. How many hours will it take them to finish this puzzle game?

One banana plant produced 120 baby bananas. Ashley went to the farm two months later and found that 30% of the bananas were ready to be harvested, so she took them home. When she returned two weeks later, 3/4 of the remaining bananas were ready, so she harvested them. After two weeks, how many bananas were not ready for harvest?
Mark buys 12 cars for his company. Each car sells for $20,000. He pays 10 percent tax on the cars, and then he pays an additional $1,000 for each one. How much does he pay for everything?

Kyle and Robert enjoy going to the beach and collecting seashells. On Monday, Kyle collects 5 more seashells than Robert collects 20. On Tuesday, Kyle collects twice as many seashells as she did on Monday.
Dax went to the orchard to gather some apples, only to find half a dozen apples in the orchard, about fifty in total.
Thirty-six penguins sunbathe in the snow; one-third jump into the sea to swim; one-third hide in caves to eat their lunch; how many penguins still sunbathe?

Steve decided to start eating more tomatoes and decided to grow his own tomato cherry. Even his girlfriend eats twice as much, 6 times a day. If a vineyard can produce 3 tomatoes a week, how much wine does it need?

John orders some pizza to share with his friends. There are 20 friends in total, and John wants to make sure that each of them can have 4 slices. Pizza is only sold sliced into 8 pieces. How many pizzas does it take for John to order?

He used a lot of pencils. He realized that by combining five of the pencils, he could make a whole pencil. If he bought 25 pencils and used the pencils to make a new one, how many pencils would he have?
John took his $20 deposit, added an additional $10 to it, and then used the money to triple his income within a year.
If Jesse is 20 years old, what is the combined age of these three girls?
If the number of students in a school is 3 A, B, and C, then 30% of the students graduate with a B, and the rest with a C.
If John has 54 caramels, how many caramels does John James have?
Dolly has two books. Pandora has one. If Dolly and Pandora both read each other's books and theirs, how many books did they end up reading together?

Mike had 5 co-writers in the company. He stopped writing to 2 of them. Each of them sent 2 letters a week that were 5 pages long. He replied the same. He could write a page in 6 minutes. How many hours a week did he spend writing?

Jason has a monthly phone plan of 1000 minutes. He has 15 minutes every day with his boss on the phone, and an additional 300 minutes this month with other people. If this month has 30 days, how many minutes does Jason have left?

Griffin had 24 french fries, but Kyle received 5. Bill received twice as many as Kyle. Ginger gave Griffin her full hand of fries, and then Colby received 3 fewer fries from Griffin than Kyle received. If Griffin ended up with 27 fries, how many Ginger fries did Kyle give Griffin?

There are 4 fish in one aquarium, and 32 in the other. The difference in the number of fish in the two aquariums is twice as large as the number of fish in the two aquariums. If the two aquariums contain the same fish, how many fish are there in each aquarium?

Jean's make-up artist charges her $250 per hour. If she needs expensive make-up for a film she's in, she needs to work 6 hours a day, 4 times a week. The film takes 5 weeks to complete. After the film is made, the make-up artist gives Jean a 10% discount due to the amount of work done. How much did Jean pay?

Isabel spent $12 for the cake, $43 for the birthday present, $15 for the flowers, $4 for the invitation, and $22 for a nice bag for the guests. She divided the cost with her two parents into three parts. How much did each person pay?
Chef bought 4 bags of chicken. Each bag weighs 50 pounds. One pound of chicken costs $1.50. How much did Chef spend?

On Monday, Sue ate four times her sister's cookie, on Tuesday she ate twice her sister's cookie, on Monday she ate five cookies, and the next day she ate 13 cookies. If one cookie has 200 calories, how many calories did Sue eat more than her sister?
